1 procedures to prevent the illegal trespass of residents onto neighboring properties, which may include setback
2 from neighboring residences, fencing, or additional staffing;
3 (b) a procedure for the department to review and approve the community home's policies and
4 procedures based on an individualized assessment of the location and unique needs of the community home
5 and consideration of the submitted public comment under subsection (4); and
6 (c) a procedure for submitting a complaint pursuant to [section 2] about a licensed community
7 home to the department.
8 (4) Prior to the grant of a license under this section, the department shall provide written notice on
9 its website and to all landowners within one-half mile of the proposed community home that it has received an
10 application for a license for a community home. The department shall allow at least 28 days from the date of the
11 notice for the public to submit comments regarding the proposed policies and procedures of the community
12 home.
13 (5) The department shall keep copies of the approved policies and procedures under subsection
14 (3) on file and provide them to a member of the public on request."
